The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 November is 8,589 (994.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 November, there were 1,027 new confirmed cases (118.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 November, there were 978 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% ( 49 extra cases).
